               </li>
             </ul>

             <ul class="grid margin-top-10">
               <li class="col-8-12">
                 <!-- <p class="lead ae-4">Although syllabi are documents used primarily by faculty and students, they often contain information for a wider range of higher education audiences.</p> -->
                 <ul class="flex margin-bottom-4">
                   <li class="col-1-12 ae-1">
                     <i class="far fa-university h2 text-gray"></i>
                   </li>
                   <li class="col-11-12 ae-2">
                     <h3 class="text-gold upppercase semiBold letter-spacing-2">THE INSTITUTION</h3>
                     <p class="lead semiBold opacity-8">The institution can require faculty to include content in their syllabi that meets accreditation standards, makes students aware of institutional policies, and promotes college values and beliefs.</p>
                   </li>
                 </ul>
                 <div class="cell-100 border padding-2 margin-5 ae-7">
                   <h5 class="text-gray margin-bottom-1 uppercase opacity-5 letter-spacing-1">EXAMPLE</h5>
